<task id="PPI-011" project="Production Performance Improvement R1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Document Intelligence Timeout and Circuit Breaker (E3)</title>
    <status>completed</status>
    <estimated-effort>3 hours</estimated-effort>
    <phase>2</phase>
    <domain>E</domain>
    <tags>bff-api, ai, resilience</tags>
    <parallel-group>P2-ALL</parallel-group>
    <dependencies>Phase 1 complete</dependencies>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    TextExtractorService.ExtractViaDocIntelAsync() uses WaitUntil.Completed with NO timeout.
    A stuck Document Intelligence request blocks the analysis indefinitely. Add a 30-second timeout
    via linked CancellationToken and a Polly circuit breaker for resilience.
  </prompt>

  <role>Senior .NET developer with Polly resilience patterns and Azure AI services expertise</role>

  <goal>
    Document Intelligence calls have a 30-second timeout. Circuit breaker opens after 3 consecutive
    failures. Graceful degradation message returned on timeout. No analysis blocks indefinitely.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="spec">projects/production-performance-improvement-r1/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="target">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/TextExtractorService.cs</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">AI features extend BFF</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-015">Log only identifiers/sizes/timings, not document content</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Return user-friendly degradation message on timeout</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <topic>resilience, circuit-breaker, document-intelligence</topic>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/constraints/ai.md</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/api/resilience.md</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/api/text-extraction.md</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/TextExtractorService.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Infrastructure/Http/ResilientHttpHandler.cs</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1" name="Locate WaitUntil.Completed call">
      Read TextExtractorService.cs (~line 519). Find the Document Intelligence call without timeout.
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Add 30-second timeout">
      Create linked CancellationTokenSource with 30-second timeout.
      Pass linked token to Document Intelligence operation.
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Add Polly circuit breaker">
      Configure circuit breaker: break after 3 consecutive failures, 60-second break duration.
      Follow pattern from ResilientHttpHandler.cs.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Add graceful degradation">
      On timeout: return user-friendly message explaining extraction took too long.
      On circuit open: return message explaining service temporarily unavailable.
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Add configuration">
      Add DocumentIntelligenceOptions with TimeoutSeconds (default 30) and CircuitBreakerThreshold.
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Test and verify">
      Run `dotnet build` and `dotnet test`.
    </step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="dotnet">Build and test .NET projects</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="code">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/TextExtractorService.cs (modified)</output>
    <output type="code">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Configuration/DocumentIntelligenceOptions.cs (modified/created)</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">Document Intelligence calls have 30-second timeout</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Circuit breaker configured with Polly</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Graceful degradation message on timeout</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Timeout configurable via DocumentIntelligenceOptions</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Build and tests pass</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
